value.title: Possible Havana syndrome incident delayed Harris flight to Vietnam
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris' departure for Vietnam was delayed by several hours Tuesday afternoon after her office was informed by the US embassy in Hanoi, Vietnam, of a "report of a recent possible anomalous health incident."

value.title: Kamala Harris calls Biden's Afghanistan decision 'courageous' as others in White House blame Trump
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris gave credit to President Biden for deciding to end the war in Afghanistan, even though members of the administration – including Biden himself – have blamed former President Trump for agreeing to withdraw U.S. troops.

value.title: Biden to be briefed on intelligence community COVID origin review as early as Tuesday
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to receive a briefing on the origin of COVID-19 from the intelligence community as early as Tuesday.

value.title: Trump calls on Florida judge to help reinstate his Youtube account
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Monday asked a Florida judge to issue a preliminary injunction in his case against YouTube that would compel the company to reinstate his access to the platform.

value.title: Harris rebukes China in major speech on Indo-Pacific
value.excerpt: U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a sharp rebuke to China for its incursions in the South China Sea, warning its actions there amount to “coercion” and “intimidation” and affirming that the U.S. will support its allies in the region against Beijing’s advances.

value.title: Hostile Trump mob sends GOP Rep. Brooks into panicked backpedal on moving on from 2020

value.title: Beijing Continues To "Coerce" And "Intimidate" In South China Sea: Kamala Harris

value.title: Why is Joe Biden suing Facebook and Instagram over vaccine posts?
value.excerpt: Facebook is back in hot water after an explosive New York Times investigative report found the company hid the truth about its most popular viral content after the company discovered the most-viewed link on the platform raised doubt about the coronavirus vaccine.

value.title: Seattle Storm visit President Biden, White House to celebrate 2020 WNBA title
value.excerpt: The Storm became the first women’s team welcomed by President Biden and the first WNBA squad at the White House since the 2015 Minnesota Lynx.

value.title: Biden praises WNBA champion Seattle Storm for their work on and off the court during White House visit
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden honored the WNBA champion Seattle Storm at the White House Monday, praising the team for its actions both on and off the court -- especially work the team has done on social justice issues.
